parameters:
\N<Segi>Lord Yuia...about your mother, the Princess Consort...you're
worried about her, aren't you?
I'm curious.
It's nothing like that.
気になる

\N<Yuia>...Yes. I'm sorry for making you worry. You must be
concerned about your parents who remained there as well...

\N<Segi>No, not at all. Besides, I'm not worried about my father and
mother. I believe they are both safe.
\N<Yuia>Is that so... You're strong, you know.

\N<Yuia>Your strength is blinding right now. I wish I could have a
bit of that strength for my cowardly self.
\N<Segi>Th-that's... If it pleases you, Lord Yuia, I am always...
\N<Yuia>Huh...?

\N<Segi>Ah, no... it's nothing... What am I saying at a time like
this...
そんな事は無い
\N<Yuia>No... it's okay. Besides, now's not the time for that.

\N<Yuia>I'm sorry for making you worry. You must be concerned about
your parents who remained there as well.

\N<Segi>No, not at all. Besides, I'm not worried about my father and
mother. I believe they are both safe.
\N<Yuia>Is that so... You're strong, you know.

\N<Yuia>Your strength is blinding right now. I wish I could have a
bit of that strength for my cowardly self.
\N<Segi>Th-that's... If it pleases you, Lord Yuia, I am always...
\N<Yuia>Huh...?

\N<Segi>Ah, no... it's nothing... What am I saying at a time like
this...
\N<Yuia>...
\N<Segi>Lord Yuia...
A
\N<Segi>Dad, Mom!
\N<Seno>Segi, I'm home now.
\N<Segi>Oh, good... Both of you are safe...

\N<Seno>Of course we are. Did you really think your father and I
would fall behind those guys?

\N<Orugi>Lord Yuia, it's a relief to see you unharmed as well. Segi,
you did well.
\N<Segi>No, I didn't do anything...

\N<Yuia>Seno, Orugi. I'm glad both of you are safe. What about
Zuuteruka and the others...?

\N<Orugi>They've retreated. However, we should consider it only
temporary. It's best to assume they will attack again soon.
\N<Yuia>...I see.

\N<Segi>Lord Yuia... I'm sorry. It's my fault that the Grand Duke
and Princess Consort's enemy...

\N<Yuia>No... that's not true. You helped me when I lost my cool and
was acting rashly.
\N<Segi>Lord Yuia...

\N<Yuia>It's the truth. If I had stayed there, I would have surely
lost my life. That wouldn't have been what my father and
mother wished for.

\N<Yuia>Segi... and you two as well, thank you. The three of you are
my lifesavers.

\N<Seno>No, we need you to live. You have an important mission to
fulfill.

\N<Seno>It's to defeat Zuuteruka and "Ryuda" and avenge His Majesty.
You can't afford to throw your life away so easily for that.
\N<Yuia>...Understood.

\N<Orugi>I may have spoken out of turn earlier. But more importantly,
we must act now.
\N<Yuia>Act...?

\N<Orugi>There is a deep cave to the north from here. It would be
wise for you to hide there for now.

\N<Orugi>Beyond the cave should lead out of the country. You should
leave this country from there.
\N<Yuia>But... I can't just run away and leave everyone behind...

\N<Orugi>Listen, Lord Yuia. Indeed, I said to avenge His Majesty, but
that time is not now.

\N<Orugi>You must gather strength and wait for the right moment. For
now, you must retreat. This is by no means a shameful
evasion.
\N<Yuia>...

\N<Seno>My husband... Orugi is right. To accomplish something,
sometimes you need to swallow your pride.

\N<Yuia>...Understood, I'll do as you two say. With my parents gone,
you two are like my surrogates...
\N<Seno>Segi, you go with him. You're going to protect Lord Yuia.
\N<Segi>But what about you and dad...?

\N<Seno>Who do you think we are? Don't make me say it again. Your
father and I won't lose to those guys.

\N<Orugi>Exactly, no need for unnecessary worries. There won't be any
problems, your mother and I will catch up soon.
\N<Segi>Okay... but please be careful...

\N<Segi>Lord Yuia... let's hurry. We don't have time to leisurely
prepare, we must leave from here at once...
\N<Orugi>...Wait.
\N<Segi>Huh?

\N<Orugi>...It's noisy outside. It seems we have some unwelcome
guests arriving.
\N<Seno>...Yes.
B
